        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cli): add skills uninstall command",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd `openclaw skills uninstall <slug>` CLI command that cleanly removes a ClawHub-installed skill from the active workspace. Mirrors the existing `skills install` flow and the `plugins uninstall` pattern.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.ts`**:\n  - Added `SkillUninstallPlan` and `SkillUninstallResult` types\n  - Added `planSkillUninstall()` - creates uninstall plan with slug validation\n  - Added `executeSkillUninstall()` - removes skill dir (only for ClawHub installs) and lockfile entry\n  - **Security fix**: Gate directory removal on ClawHub provenance (`isClawHubInstall`)\n\n- **`src/cli/skills-cli.ts`**:\n  - Added `uninstall` command with `--dry-run`, `--yes`, `--json`, `--global`, `--agent` flags\n  - **Fix**: `--json` now outputs actual result after execution\n\n## Proof\n\n### ClawHub skill uninstall with `--yes`\n```\n$ openclaw skills uninstall test-provenance --yes\nRemoved skill directory: /Users/.../.openclaw/workspace/skills/test-provenance\nRemoved lockfile entry: .clawhub/lock.json#test-provenance\nUninstalled test-provenance:\n  ✓ removed workspace directory\n  ✓ removed lockfile entry\n```\n\n### Non-ClawHub skill (now shows warning, does NOT delete)\n```\n$ openclaw skills uninstall manual-skill --yes\nSkill directory exists but is not a ClawHub install. Use \"rm -rf\" to remove manually.\nUninstalled manual-skill:\n  ✗ removed workspace directory\n  ✗ removed lockfile entry\n```\n\n### dry-run\n```\n$ openclaw skills uninstall test-skill --dry-run\nThe following would be removed:\n  - workspace directory:  .../workspace/skills/test-skill\n  - lockfile entry:       .clawhub/lock.json#test-skill\n(dry-run: no changes will be made)\n```\n\n### Non-existent skill\n```\n$ openclaw skills uninstall nonexistent\nSkill 'nonexistent' is not installed in /Users/.../.openclaw/workspace\n```\n\n## Issue\n\nFixes #63272\n\n---\n\n**Labels**: clawsweeper:fix-shape-clear, clawsweeper:queueable-fix, P2",
